<title>UK: UK manufacturing pay awards still falling - CBI.</title>
<headline>UK manufacturing pay awards still falling - CBI.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>UK manufacturing pay awards continued to fall in the third quarter of the year, the Confederation of British Industry said on Monday.</p>
<p>The CBI's latest pay databank showed provisional annual pay awards averaged 3.2 percent in the three months ending September 1996, down from 3.5 percent in the three months to June.</p>
<p>Pay awards in service firms have stabilised since the start of 1996. In the third quarter, they averaged a provisional 3.6 percent, the same as in the second quarter, the CBI said.  </p>
<p>			  MANUFACTURING FIRMS	 SERVICE FIRMS</p>
<p> September 1996	     3.2% (prov)	     3.6% (prov)</p>
<p> August			 3.3% (prov)	     3.6% (prov)</p>
<p> July			   3.3% (prov)	     3.7% (prov)</p>
<p> June			   3.5%			3.6%</p>
<p> May			    3.5%			3.5%</p>
<p> April			  3.5%			3.5%</p>
<p> January 1996		 3.6%			3.6%</p>
<p> October 1995		 3.6%			2.9%</p>
<p> July			   3.3%			3.7%</p>
<p> April			  3.3%			3.4%</p>
<p> January			3.1%			3.3%</p>
